      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Strip your<strong> rosemary leaves</strong> off their stems (discard the stems) and chop finely</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries, then add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>rosemary </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt, </strong>then put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1653317805970-x200.jpg",
